          help = [[

LAMMPS is a classical molecular dynamics code, and an acronym for Large-scale Atomic/Molecular Massively Parallel Simulator.
LAMMPS has potentials for solid-state materials (metals, semiconductors) and soft matter (biomolecules, polymers) and coarse-grained or mesoscopic systems. It can be used to model atoms or, more generically, as a parallel particle simulator at the atomic, meso, or continuum scale. LAMMPS runs on single processors or in parallel using message-passing techniques and a spatial-decomposition of the simulation domain. Many of its models have versions that provide accelerated performance on CPUs, GPUs, and Intel Xeon Phis. The code is designed to be easy to modify or extend with new functionality.

Most packages are enabled for this build of LAMMPS, and GPUs, OpenMP, and MPI are all supported within this build as well. It is recommened to use intel/2025 implementations of these supported functions. The only unavailable packages for this build are ADIOS, KOKKOS, ML-QUIP, and VTK. Note that the availability of some packages depends upon the intended use of LAMMPS with respect to the hardware utilized and the parallelization options used.

The following executables are available within this module:
  - lmp_omp: OpenMP functionality enabled
  - lmp_mpi: OpenMP and MPI functionality enabled (must use `mpirun` command before lmp_gpu)
  - lmp_gpu: OpenMP, MPI, and GPU functionality enabled (only usable on a GPU (p-gc-*) node and must use `mpirun` command before lmp_gpu)
  * by default, the `lmp` command utilizes the lmp_omp executable


]],
